1. What is a block?
- It is code that is put between tow curly braces { }
2. Does a C program start at the beginning ? Where is the beginning?
- No, preprocessor code and declarations ..
3. What happens when a program comes to a '}' character ? What does this
character signify ?
- It halts, end of instructions
4. What vital piece of punctuation goes at the end of every simple C statement?
- ;
5. What happens if a  comment is not ended? Tha is if the programmer types '/*'
to start but forgets the .. '*/' to close ?
- Everything after the comment becomes part of it (till the end of line or
the end of program) , an unclosed /* means all the lines after it are part of
the comment
